      • getParentContainerId

        public long getParentContainerId()
        Description copied from interface: FlowNodeInstance
        Returns the task's direct container ID. For a sub-task or CallActivity, would point to the containing activity ID of the current element. For a normal Task / Activity, would point to the ID of the process instance containing the task / activity. For a multi-instanciated task, each task has its parentContainerId pointing to the containing multi-instance task (basic container for all task instances).
        Specified by:
        getParentContainerId in interface FlowNodeInstance
        Returns:
        the ID of the direct containing element (activity instance of process instance).
